  "title": "Anomaly as Discovery Signal",
  "concept": "When measured results exceed what your model predicts, the gap itself is the data—it tells you which simplifications in your theory are hiding real interactions.",
  "interactiveId": "720e8684-3329-4482-86df-5ae86e4a1cb3",
  "sourcePieceId": "b9635350-3c1f-4418-a6ae-b242e9ed7ce1",
  "publishedAt": 1778436416296,
  "voiceScore": 94,
  "content": {
    "type": "html",
    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<title>Anomaly as Discovery Signal</title>\n<style>\n  :root {\n    --bg: #faf7f1;\n    --fg: #1a1a1a;\n    --muted: #6b6b6b;\n    --line: #e5e0d6;\n    --predict: #4a90e2;\n    --actual: #e85d75;\n    --gap: #f4a261;\n  }\n  * { box-sizing: border-box; }\n  body {\n    font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", sans-serif;\n    margin: 0;\n    padding: 20px;\n    color: var(--fg);\n    background: var(--bg);\n    line-height: 1.5;\n  }\n  h2 {\n    font-size: 1.05rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    margin: 0 0 4px;\n  }\n  p.subhead {\n    margin: 0 0 20px;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .controls {\n    margin-bottom: 24px;\n  }\n  .control {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 14px;\n    margin-bottom: 12px;\n  }\n  .control label {\n    font-weight: 500;\n    flex-shrink: 0;\n    min-width: 90px;\n  }\n  .control input[type=range] {\n    flex: 1;\n    accent-color: var(--predict);\n    min-width: 120px;\n  }\n  .control output {\n    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    min-width: 3.5ch;\n    text-align: right;\n  }\n  .chart-container {\n    margin: 24px 0;\n    padding: 20px;\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n  }\n  .bars {\n    display: flex;\n    gap: 32px;\n    align-items: flex-end;\n    height: 200px;\n    margin-bottom: 16px;\n  }\n  .bar-group {\n    flex: 1;\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: column;\n    align-items: center;\n    height: 100%;\n  }\n  .bar {\n    width: 60px;\n    background: var(--predict);\n    border-radius: 4px 4px 0 0;\n    position: relative;\n    transition: height 200ms ease-out;\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: column;\n    justify-content: flex-end;\n  }\n  .bar.actual {\n    background: var(--actual);\n  }\n  .bar-label {\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    margin-top: 8px;\n    text-align: center;\n    color: var(--muted);\n  }\n  .bar-value {\n    font-size: 0.7rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    color: #fff;\n    padding: 4px;\n    text-align: center;\n  }\n  .gap-indicator {\n    position: absolute;\n    left: 50%;\n    transform: translateX(-50%);\n    width: 80px;\n    text-align: center;\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    color: var(--gap);\n    pointer-events: none;\n  }\n  .reading {\n    margin: 18px 0 6px;\n    padding: 10px 14px;\n    background: var(--bg);\n    border: 1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .reading strong {\n    font-weight: 600;\n  }\n  .reading .gap-text {\n    color: var(--gap);\n    font-weight: 600;\n  }\n  p.caption {\n    margin: 14px 0 0;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.875rem;\n  }\n  .legend {\n    display: flex;\n    gap: 20px;\n    margin-top: 12px;\n    font-size: 0.8rem;\n  }\n  .legend-item {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 6px;\n  }\n  .legend-box {\n    width: 16px;\n    height: 16px;\n    border-radius: 2px;\n  }\n  @media (max-width: 480px) {\n    .bars {\n      gap: 20px;\n    }\n    .bar {\n      width: 50px;\n    }\n    .control label {\n      min-width: 70px;\n      font-size: 0.9rem;\n    }\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h2>Adjust the variables — watch the prediction miss</h2>\n<p class=\"subhead\">Your model adds up known effects. Real results sometimes exceed that sum.</p>\n\n<div class=\"controls\">\n  <div class=\"control\">\n    <label for=\"var-a\">Variable A:</label>\n    <input id=\"var-a\" type=\"range\" min=\"0\" max=\"50\" value=\"30\" aria-describedby=\"var-a-out\">\n    <output id=\"var-a-out\" for=\"var-a\">30</output>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"control\">\n    <label for=\"var-b\">Variable B:</label>\n    <input id=\"var-b\" type=\"range\" min=\"0\" max=\"50\" value=\"25\" aria-describedby=\"var-b-out\">\n    <output id=\"var-b-out\" for=\"var-b\">25</output>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"control\">\n    <label for=\"var-c\">Variable C:</label>\n    <input id=\"var-c\" type=\"range\" min=\"0\" max=\"30\" value=\"15\" aria-describedby=\"var-c-out\">\n    <output id=\"var-c-out\" for=\"var-c\">15</output>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"chart-container\">\n  <div class=\"bars\">\n    <div class=\"bar-group\">\n      <div class=\"bar\" id=\"predicted-bar\">\n        <div class=\"bar-value\" id=\"predicted-value\">70</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"bar-label\">Model<br>prediction</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"bar-group\" style=\"position: relative;\">\n      <div class=\"gap-indicator\" id=\"gap-indicator\" style=\"bottom: 0;\">Gap: <span id=\"gap-value\">22</span></div>\n      <div class=\"bar actual\" id=\"actual-bar\">\n        <div class=\"bar-value\" id=\"actual-value\">92</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"bar-label\">Measured<br>result</div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  \n  <div class=\"legend\">\n    <div class=\"legend-item\">\n      <div class=\"legend-box\" style=\"background: var(--predict);\"></div>\n      <span>Predicted (sum of variables)</span>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"legend-item\">\n      <div class=\"legend-box\" style=\"background: var(--actual);\"></div>\n      <span>Actual measurement</span>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"reading\">\n  Model predicts: <strong id=\"predict-text\">70</strong>. \n  You measured: <strong id=\"measure-text\">92</strong>. \n  <span class=\"gap-text\">Gap: <span id=\"gap-text\">22</span></span> — <span id=\"interpretation\">something in the combination produces an effect your variables don't capture</span>.\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"caption\" id=\"caption\">When measured performance beats the sum of known parts, the gap points to an interaction your model missed.</p>\n\n<script>\n  (function () {\n    var sliders = {\n      a: document.getElementById('var-a'),\n      b: document.getElementById('var-b'),\n      c: document.getElementById('var-c')\n    };\n    var outputs = {\n      a: document.getElementById('var-a-out'),\n      b: document.getElementById('var-b-out'),\n      c: document.getElementById('var-c-out')\n    };\n    var predictedBar = document.getElementById('predicted-bar');\n    var predictedValue = document.getElementById('predicted-value');\n    var actualBar = document.getElementById('actual-bar');\n    var actualValue = document.getElementById('actual-value');\n    var gapIndicator = document.getElementById('gap-indicator');\n    var gapValue = document.getElementById('gap-value');\n    var predictText = document.getElementById('predict-text');\n    var measureText = document.getElementById('measure-text');\n    var gapText = document.getElementById('gap-text');\n    var interpretation = document.getElementById('interpretation');\n    var caption = document.getElementById('caption');\n\n    function update() {\n      var a = +sliders.a.value;\n      var b = +sliders.b.value;\n      var c = +sliders.c.value;\n\n      outputs.a.textContent = a;\n      outputs.b.textContent = b;\n      outputs.c.textContent = c;\n\n      // Model prediction: simple sum of variables\n      var predicted = a + b + c;\n\n      // Actual: sum plus a bonus from interaction terms that scales\n      // with how balanced the variables are (simulates emergent behavior\n      // from combinations). Peak bonus when all three are roughly equal.\n      var balance = 1 - (Math.max(a, b, c) - Math.min(a, b, c)) / 100;\n      var interactionBonus = Math.floor(balance * 25);\n      var actual = predicted + interactionBonus;\n\n      var gap = actual - predicted;\n\n      // Update bars (scale to 200px max height for visualization)\n      var maxHeight = 200;\n      var scale = maxHeight / 130; // max possible is ~130\n      predictedBar.style.height = (predicted * scale) + 'px';\n      actualBar.style.height = (actual * scale) + 'px';\n\n      predictedValue.textContent = predicted;\n      actualValue.textContent = actual;\n      gapValue.textContent = gap;\n      predictText.textContent = predicted;\n      measureText.textContent = actual;\n      gapText.textContent = gap;\n\n      // Position gap indicator between the bars\n      var predictedHeight = predicted * scale;\n      gapIndicator.style.bottom = predictedHeight + 'px';\n\n      // Update interpretation and caption based on gap size\n      if (gap === 0) {\n        interpretation.textContent = 'prediction matches measurement — model is complete';\n        caption.textContent = 'No gap means your model captures all the effects. No anomaly, no discovery.';\n      } else if (gap < 8) {\n        interpretation.textContent = 'small gap — might be measurement noise, might be a hint';\n        caption.textContent = 'A tiny gap could be error, or it could point to a weak interaction your variables miss.';\n      } else if (gap < 15) {\n        interpretation.textContent = 'clear gap — something in the combination produces an effect your variables don\\'t capture';\n        caption.textContent = 'When measured performance beats the sum of known parts, the gap points to an interaction your model missed.';\n      } else {\n        interpretation.textContent = 'large gap — a major interaction is invisible to your current model';\n        caption.textContent = 'A big anomaly says your simplifications hid something real. The gap is the discovery.';\n      }\n    }\n\n    sliders.a.addEventListener('input', update);\n    sliders.b.addEventListener('input', update);\n    sliders.c.addEventListener('input', update);\n    update();\n  })();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
